<br>
From here on I am only doing planning for Strike Force level hits for epics, so I look at the top thread to determine which final parts people are on that require the army.<br>
<br>
Please keep your top post in this forum updated.  If you get a hit done update it, it lets me know when you are in the zone for a strike force hit.<br>
<br>
This type of effort I see as the following places:<br>
<br>
Fear<br>
Chardok<br>
Trakanon (Old Sebelis)<br>
<br>
With the exception of those places - ALL remaining epic hits are either 1 or 2 groupable, OR are mobolization mobs that we normally get an army strength for, sometimes overkill - but overkill on a mobo day = more mobo/contested spawns.<br>
<br>
Left Sky off because well - there will be one trip to sky in a couple months to farm some Spiroc blades for warriors and MQ sales, but essentially we need no more drops from there except for mebe some SK blades, and only 1 Current TFer is even working his SK epic - that I know of - Aboo, and he has his.<br>
<br>
Left Hate off because I have been there. All epic hits in Hate are one groupable.<br>
<br>
Back to the point.  Feel free to post any epic hit you are planning in this forum for Wednesday nights and Saturday days and Sundays.  Or for earlier in the day on other days if you think that there is any viable player base available at the time as to not to conflict with scheduled Guild raids.  Remember I am requesting that no one schedules anything larger than 1 group affairs for mondays.  Recognize that peeps will sign up for some based on availability and some will just show up if they are online when you go.  Remember peeps - if you are posting epic completion hits.... It would behoove you to sign up for each others hits.  Likewise if someone posts an epic completion hit and /cough they were at yours, it would also behoove you to sign up and support thiers. <br>
<br>
I will not likely sign up for most of these.  I have encouraged you to plan these events at times when I KNOW I will be less likely to be available. Most of my availablilty is tapped out on the scheduled guild days which limits hardly any other online time.  I will offer you this:  IF; IF, I can go and I am there AND you would like me to run it, that is fine.  Having run or attended just about every epic encounter that requires more than one group, it is possible that I might be able to make the hit go smooth.<br>
<br>
What will I plan?<br>
<br>
Once a month I will be running a maximum of 1 trip to chardok and when there is space taking a raid to Fear, depending on the rest of the months schedule.  To epic bards, There will be some incident of us taking down Trak and then returning the next day or 2 days later to do turn in to the Undead Bard.  Trak is on our list of mobo mobs but a lot of issues with him is knowing he is up, and not having any easier to get to mobs avail.<br>
<br>
IN Other words people.,  use this forum to:<br>
1. post your checklist on the top forum and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>don't clutter the page with a repeat of what is in the checklist. </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
2.Post epic hits that you are hosting for yourself or for someone else in this forum and ensure the end time doesn't come within 45 minutes of conflicting with guild raid schedules.<br>
